OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FWhat can we gather from the results of
OL,6,FThursday's elections? ITV News
OL,7,FElection Analysist Professor Jane
OL,8,FGreen gives her take
OL,10,FBy Jane Green and Marta Miori,
OL,11,FNuffield College, University of Oxford
OL,13,FAfter a day of results coming in, we
OL,14,Fnow know enough about these local and
OL,15,Fdevolved elections to start
OL,16,Fidentifying the broader patterns
OL,17,Femerging across Britain ` and to
OL,18,Fassess whether these elections
OL,19,Fconfirmed what we already thought was
OL,20,Fhappening in British politics, or
OL,21,Fwhether they revealed something new.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FOne new thing we've learned is that
OL,6,FLabour is doing worse in its heartland
OL,7,Fareas, where people voted more
OL,8,Fstrongly for Leave. These are areas
OL,9,Fwhere the potential support for Reform
OL,10,Fis simply higher.
OL,12,FThe split in Labour's vote (left and
OL,13,Fright) will be making it much easier
OL,14,Ffor Reform to do well, and Reform will
OL,15,Fbe taking votes from the Conservatives
OL,16,Fwho, the last time these elections
OL,17,Fwere fought, were still being led by
OL,18,FBoris Johnson and support for Boris's
OL,19,FBrexit had not yet waned.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FThe greater loss of Labour support in
OL,6,FLeave areas is a replay of what
OL,7,Fhappened to the Conservatives in the
OL,8,F2024 general election, who lost most
OL,9,Fsupport where they had done well after
OL,10,FBrexit.
OL,12,FIt is also, to a large extent, these
OL,13,Fareas catching up with the broader
OL,14,Ftransformation of Labour's electoral
OL,15,Fcoalition up to 2024, as the party
OL,16,Fincreasingly came to perform better in
OL,17,Fareas with more graduates and
OL,18,Fprofessionals.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FThe other insight is that, in a highly
OL,6,Ffragmented election, some places are
OL,7,Fseeing very high levels of splintering
OL,8,Fwhile others are showing signs of
OL,9,Fgreater coordination around a smaller
OL,10,Fnumber of parties.
OL,12,FWe expected voters in different places
OL,13,Fwould coalesce behind different types
OL,14,Fof parties ` with the Lib Dems doing
OL,15,Fbetter in affluent areas, Greens in
OL,16,Furban and younger areas, Labour and
OL,17,Fthe Greens in areas where there are
OL,18,Fmore graduates ` like we've seen in
OL,19,Frecent by-elections.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FThat's true in some of the results. In
OL,6,Fothers, the picture is far more evenly
OL,7,Ffragmented.
OL,9,FThis is going to mean that, in some
OL,10,Fplaces, political parties can
OL,11,Fgenuinely argue that the race now
OL,12,Fboils down to a clearer contest
OL,13,Fbetween the most viable parties on the
OL,14,Fleft and right.
OL,16,FIn others, the races are becoming
OL,17,Fextraordinarily competitive between
OL,18,Fmultiple parties ` and those places
OL,19,Fwill become some of the most marginal
OL,20,Fand politically important contests
OL,21,Fmoving forward.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FCrucially, however, despite various
OL,6,Fpolitical attempts to say these
OL,7,Felections herald major breakthroughs
OL,8,For disappointing wake up calls, the
OL,9,Freality is that the results are
OL,10,Fotherwise entirely in line with what
OL,11,Fwe knew already.
OL,13,FThe polls that predicted losses for
OL,14,Fboth Labour and the Conservatives have
OL,15,Fborne out. The significance of that
OL,16,Fshouldn't be underestimated.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FThis is dire for Labour only two years
OL,6,Finto government, starting that period
OL,7,Fon an historically low vote share for
OL,8,Fany party governing alone. It is only
OL,9,Fgetting worse for Labour.
OL,11,FFor the Conservatives, it is almost
OL,12,Funheard of for the main party in
OL,13,Fopposition to continue to lose
OL,14,Fsupport. Usually, they would be
OL,15,Fexpecting to make gains from Labour's
OL,16,Fwoes. They're not. They're continuing
OL,17,Fto go backwards. And this is being
OL,18,Fconfirmed in today's results.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FReform have been the clear winners in
OL,6,FEngland. But this is a continuation of
OL,7,Fwhat we saw in the May 2025 local
OL,8,Felections.
OL,10,FThere is certainly plenty for Reform
OL,11,Fto celebrate, but the results show
OL,12,Fthat the party is maintaining its
OL,13,Flevel of support rather than building
OL,14,Fsubstantially (at least so far) ` and
OL,15,Fit may even be slightly down once the
OL,16,Ffinal overall vote shares are fully
OL,17,Fcomparable with last year.
OL,19,FIn other words: Reform are
OL,20,Fconsolidating their support, rather
OL,21,Fthan making another major leap forward.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FOverall, voters are opting for
OL,6,Fchallengers to a degree we've never
OL,7,Fseen before. This is exactly in line
OL,8,Fwith what the polls have been showing.
OL,9,FBroadly, survey data tells us that
OL,10,Fmost people who voted for a 'left'
OL,11,Fparty previously are choosing a
OL,12,Fdifferent left party. Most people who
OL,13,Fvoted for a 'right' party are choosing
OL,14,Fa different right party.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FThis has all kinds of fascinating
OL,6,Fconsequences. In Wales it looks like a
OL,7,Freplacement of two-partyism, not a
OL,8,Frejection of it. After all, the choice
OL,9,Fstill comes down to which party on a
OL,10,Fvoter's side is best placed to beat a
OL,11,Fparty on the other, but with Labour
OL,12,Fbeing effectively replaced by Plaid
OL,13,FCymru and the Conservatives by Reform.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FIn England, the bar is now unusually
OL,6,Flow for other parties to leapfrog
OL,7,Fover. So, Reform can do well on a
OL,8,Fmodest vote share (by historic
OL,9,Fstandards for 'winners') simply
OL,10,Fbecause Labour and the Conservatives
OL,11,Fhave lowered the threshold for them to
OL,12,Fjump over.
OL,14,FBut remember, while we will hear much
OL,15,Ftalk of a 'Reform surge', this isn't a
OL,16,Fnew surge this May, but these seats
OL,17,F(which were last fought in 2022)
OL,18,Fcatching up with political change post-
OL,19,F2024 and the results we saw in 2025.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FThe 'lower threshold' explanation is
OL,6,Falso crucial in Scotland where
OL,7,FReform's relative breakthrough in
OL,8,Fseats will still be on a low vote
OL,9,Fshare compared to their vote share in
OL,10,FEngland. It's also the reason the SNP
OL,11,Fwill still hold most of the seats
OL,12,Fwhile their vote share is
OL,13,Fsignificantly down.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FAs for the Greens? They have been
OL,6,Fdoing much better in the polls, and
OL,7,Fthat's reflected in council gains, but
OL,8,Fthey still may be struggling to quite
OL,9,Fdo well enough to fully translate that
OL,10,Fvote share into a comparable seat
OL,11,Fshare (because our electoral system
OL,12,Fstill benefits parties in the lead).
OL,14,FThey're getting into second or third
OL,15,Fplace and may need a few more heaves
OL,16,Fto translate that into lots of first-
OL,17,Fplace gains. All expected.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
