OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,6,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,7,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,8,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,10,FThe Lib Dems are quietly having a good
OL,11,Fset of results, holding quite steady
OL,12,Fin the polls. They would need a
OL,13,Fsignificant improvement in their
OL,14,Fpublic support to make greater gains,
OL,15,Fbut their vote tends to be very
OL,16,F'efficient' (geographically
OL,17,Fconcentrated in a way that means they
OL,18,Fcan do well in seats on their vote
OL,19,Fshare).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FWe don't expect Ed Davey to be losing
OL,6,Fmuch sleep over a failure to 'surge'
OL,7,Fgiven their support is roughly
OL,8,Fequivalent to the support that
OL,9,Fdelivered them a huge 72 MPs in
OL,10,Fparliament in 2024, and also because
OL,11,Fthey will also benefit from the much
OL,12,Flower thresholds they need to jump
OL,13,Fover. Politics has got easier for the
OL,14,Fchallengers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30716
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FTurnout is up (but still low in
OL,6,Fcomparison to general elections).
OL,7,FThat's entirely in line with the by-
OL,8,Felections we've seen since 2024 and
OL,9,Fthe fact that these elections will
OL,10,Ffeel higher stakes in a world where
OL,11,Fpeople may more strongly fear or
OL,12,Fdislike a party on the other 'side'
OL,13,Fand want to express their
OL,14,Fdissatisfaction with the status quo.
OL,15,FAnd turnout is typically higher again
OL,16,Fin the devolved elections in the
OL,17,Fnations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30717
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778292208
OL,3,CElections 2026. What have we learned?
OL,5,FSo far, then, the results of these
OL,6,Felections are not 'new news' despite
OL,7,Fwhat the political parties may say.
OL,8,FThe results are broadly in line with
OL,9,Ftheir expectations.
OL,11,FNevertheless, there's nothing like
OL,12,Freal votes to focus the mind when
OL,13,Fpolls can be wilfully ignored in place
OL,14,Fof wishful thinking.
OL,16,FThese elections are still a hugely
OL,17,Fimportant democratic moment that will
OL,18,Ffocus political minds, shape politics
OL,19,Fand, of course, shape how we are
OL,20,Fgoverned locally across Great Britain.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
